{
  "texts": [
    "Schölkopf et al. (2001) representer theorem proves that the optimal solution to a class of L 2 regularized functions can be reformulated as a weighted sum of the training data in kernel form.",
    "Put simply, representer methods decompose the predictions of specific model classes into the individual contributions (i.e., influence) of each training instance.",
    "This makes influence estimation a natural application of the representer theorem.",
    "Consider regularized empirical risk minimization where optimal parameters satisfy.",
    "20 with 𝜆 > 0 the L 2 regularization strength."
  ]
}